node.text:
Last week, I had camping permits to a spot in the Rockies that I’ve wanted to camp at for years🏔 I was so incredibly stoked, but the smoke from the wildfires made me change my plans.

So, my friends and I decided to head to Vancouver Island instead. I’ve always had a list of hikes I wanted to crush there but the Rockies always took priority for me so I hadn’t got to many yet.

After five days of hiking on the island, I am completely in love with the area. There’s so much to explore and I can’t wait to show you more of it! I swear BC just gets better… and better… and better🌲🇨🇦

PS. I have so many DMs right now about my Vancouver Island trip and there’s no way I can answer them all🥲 I’ll try my best, but if I don’t get back to you, just know that I’ll be writing a blog post on the island soon. I just want to cross off a few more hikes before sharing the info with you. So stay tuned!

Photo shot by @brendinkelly
